  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Local Cooperation Fund (LCF) in Zambia</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project objectives are: 1. To establish sustainable community social auditing systems in Chipata District as a tool for tracking Constituency Development Fund expenditure by 2012, 2. To enhance support for planning and implementation of relevant community-owned CDF-funded projects where  impacts are visible and therefore better future management of CDF funds, 3. To establish sustainable linkages between the community in Chipata district and active stakeholders in addressing governance accountability, corruption and abuse of public funds for enhanced governance accountability and community participation at all levels of public expenditure by 2014, 4. To document and share the experiences of social auditing in Chipata district which will inform CDFA public policy engagement for more evidence-based policy engagement by 2014 and beyond.</narrative>
  </description>
